ğŸ“ What is File Naming Convention in Java?
Java file name = name of the public class inside it + .java extension
âœ… Basic Rules:
1ï¸âƒ£ File name must match the public class name

2ï¸âƒ£ Use PascalCase for class/file names
Means: Each word starts with a capital letter
âœ… Examples:
MyFirstProgram.java
StudentDetails.java
HelloWorld.java

3ï¸âƒ£ Avoid special characters
âŒ Donâ€™t use: @, #, %, space, -
âœ… Use only letters, numbers, and underscores (if really needed â€” but better to use PascalCase).

4ï¸âƒ£ File extension must be .java
For all Java source files, the extension must be .java



